{"title_page": "2009 A Lyga", "text_new": "{{infobox football league season\n| competition      = [[A Lyga]]\n| season           = 2009\n| winners          = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]<br/>5th league title\n| relegated        = \n| continentalcup1  = [[2010\u201311 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK V\u0117tra|V\u0117tra]]<br/>[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]<br/>TBD (via [[2009\u201310 Lithuanian Football Cup|dom. cup]])\n| continentalcup3  = [[2010\u201311 Baltic League|Baltic League]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]<br/>[[FK V\u0117tra|V\u0117tra]]<br/>[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]<br/>[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]]<br/>[[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]]\n| league topscorer = [[Valdas Trakys]] (20)\n| biggest home win = [[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]] 6-0 [[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]\n| biggest away win = [[FK LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas|LKKA ir Teledema]] 2-7 [[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]] <br> [[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]] 0-5 [[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]] <br> [[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]] 0-5 [[FK V\u0117tra|V\u0117tra]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas|LKKA ir Teledema]] 2-7 [[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]\n| matches          = 112\n| total goals      = 302\n| prevseason       = [[2008 A Lyga|2008]]\n| nextseason       = [[2010 A Lyga|2010]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Lithuanian [[A Lyga]] 2009''' was the 20th season of top-tier football in Lithuania. The season started on 4 April 2009<ref name=\"finalClassification\">{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/,nid.2641 |title=A lygoje \"Kauno\", \"Atlanto\", ir \"\u017dalgirio\" nebus |date=27 March 2009 |publisher=www.futbolas.lt |language=Lithuanian |accessdate=28 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090328093413/http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/%2Cnid.2641 |archivedate=28 March 2009 |url-status=dead }} </ref> and ended on 31 October 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/,nid.2663 |title=Paskelbtas 2009 met\u0173 A lygos sezono tvarkara\u0161tis |date=30 March 2009 |publisher=www.futbolas.lt |language=Lithuanian |accessdate=30 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090331231058/http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/%2Cnid.2663 |archivedate=31 March 2009 |url-status=dead }} </ref> [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]] successfully defended their title.\n\n==Promotion and relegation==\n[[FK \u0160ilut\u0117|\u0160ilut\u0117]] were relegated to the [[I Lyga]] after finishing the [[A Lyga 2008|2008 season]] in last place. They were replaced by I Lyga champions [[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]].\n\n==Pre-season controversy==\nThe [[Lithuania]]n top [[Association football|football]] division was shaken to its core after [[FBK Kaunas]] and [[FK Atlantas|Atlantas]] withdrew their participation on 20 March 2009. Both teams cited serious differences with the [[Lithuanian Football Federation]] over the way the league has been led in the past as a reason.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/,nid.2585 |title=A lygos likimas spr\u0119sis po savait\u0117s, \"Kaunas\" ir \"Atlantas\" traukiasi, \"\u017dalgiriui\" vil\u010di\u0173 yra |date=20 March 2009 |publisher=www.futbolas.lt |language=Lithuanian |accessdate=21 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090322004043/http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/%2Cnid.2585 |archivedate=22 March 2009 |url-status=dead }} </ref> This was the second blow to the league within two weeks after [[FK \u017dalgiris Vilnius|\u017dalgiris]] were denied a license for this season because of excessive financial problems on 6 March 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.15min.lt/naujiena/sportas/futbolas/24/31464/|title=No exemption for legendary club ''(Legendiniam klubui i\u0161imtis nepadaryta)''|date=7 March 2009|publisher=www.15min.lt|language=Lithuanian|accessdate=11 March 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090409210359/http://www.15min.lt/naujiena/sportas/futbolas/24/31464/|archivedate=2009-04-09|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAs a consequence, the chairman of the National Football Clubs' Association (NFKA), [[Gintaras Ugianskis]], resigned from his post. Further, the organization of the league was put into the hands of the LFF.<ref name=\"ALygaDecisions\">{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolas.lt/en/news/,nid.2593 |title=Final decisions on A lyga to be made on March 27th |date=21 March 2009 |publisher=www.futbolas.lt |accessdate=23 March 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408062918/http://www.futbolas.lt/en/news/%2Cnid.2593 |archivedate=8 April 2009 }}</ref>\n\nThe 2009 A Lyga consists of eight teams chosen from all teams of both [[A Lyga]] and I Lyga. Teams with a higher 2008 season rank had a preference to enter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/,nid.2623 |title=A lygoje \u017eaisti sutikt\u0173 bent trys I lygos klubai |date=25 March 2009 |publisher=www.futbolas.lt |language=Lithuanian |accessdate=25 March 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090326025517/http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/naujienos/%2Cnid.2623 |archivedate=26 March 2009 |url-status=dead }} </ref> Clubs being interested in a participation could submit their application until 26 March 2009.<ref name=\"ALygaDecisions\" />\n\nOn 27 March 2009, the LFF announced the three replacement teams. [[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga Garg\u017edai]], [[FK LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas|LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas]] and [[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja Pakruojis]] were appointed to the league.<ref name=\"finalClassification\" />\nFurther, the LFF classified FBK Kaunas and Atlantas to play in the third-tier [[II Lyga]] because of \"unethical conduct and other irregularities\" while \u017dalgiris were granted a license for the second-level I Lyga.<ref name=\"finalClassification\" />\n\n==Clubs==\n{{Location map+|Lithuania|float=right|width=290|caption=Location of teams in the '''A Lyga 2009'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.712778|long=21.403333|label=[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.733333|long=24.35|label=[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.966667|long=23.866667|label=[[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.9|long=23.933333|label=[[FK LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas|LKKA&nbsp;ir&nbsp;Teledema]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.933333|long=23.316667|label=[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.566667|long=23.35|label=[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.25|long=22.283333|label=[[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.683333|long=25.283333|label=[[FK V\u0117tra|V\u0117tra]]}}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Club\n!Location\n!Stadium\n!Capacity\n!Current manager\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]||[[Garg\u017edai]] \n|[[Garg\u017edai Stadium]]\n|800\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Vytautas Jan\u010diauskas]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]||[[Panev\u0117\u017eys]]\n|[[Auk\u0161taitija Stadium]]\n|4,000\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Valdas Urbonas]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]||[[Pakruojis]]\n|[[Pakruojis Stadium]]\n|1,000\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Aidas Dambrauskas]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas|LKKA ir Teledema]]||[[Kaunas]]\n|[[Kaunas L\u017d\u016aU stadium]]\n|1,000\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Via\u010dislavas Novikovas]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]||[[Marijampol\u0117]]\n|[[S\u016bduva stadium|S\u016bduva Stadium]]\n|6,260\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Gedeminas Jarmalavi\u010dius]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]]||[[\u0160iauliai]]\n|[[Savivaldyb\u0117 Stadium]]\n|2,430\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Deivis Kan\u010delskis]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]]||[[Taurag\u0117]]\n|[[Vytauto Stadium]]\n|1,600\n|{{flagicon|Latvia}} [[Jurijs Popkovs]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[FK V\u0117tra|V\u0117tra]]||[[Vilnius]]\n|[[V\u0117tra Stadium]]\n|5,300\n|{{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Virginijus Liub\u0161ys]]\n|}\n\n==League table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=EKR|name_EKR=[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]\n|team2=V\u0116T|name_V\u0116T=[[FK V\u0117tra|V\u0117tra]]\n|team3=S\u016aD|name_S\u016aD=[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]\n|team4=\u0160IA|name_\u0160IA=[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]]\n|team5=TAU|name_TAU=[[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]]\n|team6=BAN|name_BAN=[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]\n|team7=L&T|name_L&T=[[FK LKKA ir Teledema Kaunas|LKKA ir Teledema]]\n|team8=KRU|name_KRU=[[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]\n|win_EKR=18|draw_EKR=9|loss_EKR=1|gf_EKR=58|ga_EKR=20|status_EKR=C\n|win_V\u0116T=16|draw_V\u0116T=9|loss_V\u0116T=3|gf_V\u0116T=55|ga_V\u0116T=22\n|win_S\u016aD=14|draw_S\u016aD=11|loss_S\u016aD=3|gf_S\u016aD=55|ga_S\u016aD=22\n|win_\u0160IA=13|draw_\u0160IA=3|loss_\u0160IA=12|gf_\u0160IA=40|ga_\u0160IA=34\n|win_TAU=10|draw_TAU=8|loss_TAU=10|gf_TAU=26|ga_TAU=22\n|win_BAN=7|draw_BAN=6|loss_BAN=15|gf_BAN=25|ga_BAN=49\n|win_L&T=4|draw_L&T=3|loss_L&T=21|gf_L&T=19|ga_L&T=63\n|win_KRU=2|draw_KRU=7|loss_KRU=19|gf_KRU=24|ga_KRU=70\n\n|note_V\u0116T=V\u0117tra were denied the UEFA license for the 2010\u201311 season and therefore will not represent Lithuania in the UEFA Europa League.<ref>[http://www.futbolas.lt/2010/05/03/%e2%80%9evetra%e2%80%9c-siemet-negales-rungtyniauti-uefa-europos-lygoje/ \u201eV\u0117tra\u201c \u0161iemet negal\u0117s rungtyniauti UEFA Europos lygoje] {{in lang|lt}}</ref> Since the finalists of the [[2009\u201310 Lithuanian Football Cup]] are V\u0117tra and Champions League-qualified Ekranas, all Europa League spots were awarded to teams based on their league positions. Therefore, S\u016bduva and \u0160iauliai qualified for the [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|second]], while Tauras qualified for the [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|first qualifying round]] of the UEFA Europa League.\n|note_\u0160IA=V\u0116T\n|note_TAU=V\u0116T\n\n|col_CL2=green1|text_CL2=Qualification to [[2010\u201311 UEFA Champions League#Second qualifying round|Champions League second qualifying round]]\n|result1=CL2\n|col_EL2=blue1|text_EL2=Qualification to [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|Europa League second qualifying round]]\n|result3=EL2|result4=EL2\n|col_EL1=blue2|text_EL1=Qualification to [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|Europa League first qualifying round]]\n|result5=EL1\n\n|update=complete\n|source=[https://web.archive.org/web/20090410022453/http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/lygos/a-lyga futbolas.lt] {{in lang|lt}}\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) head-to-head points; 3) head-to-head goal difference; 4) head-to-head goals scored; 5) goal difference; 6) number of goals scored.\n}}\n\n==Results==\nEvery team will play each other four times, twice at home and twice on the road, for a total of 28 games.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{#invoke:sports results|main\n|title=First half of season\n|matches_style=FBR|solid_cell=grey\n|team1=BAN|team2=EKR|team3=KRU|team4=L&T|team5=S\u016aD\n|team6=\u0160IA|team7=TAU|team8=V\u0116T\n\n|name_BAN=[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]\n|match_BAN_EKR=1\u20132\n|match_BAN_KRU=3\u20130\n|match_BAN_L&T=1\u20130\n|match_BAN_S\u016aD=0\u20130\n|match_BAN_\u0160IA=3\u20132\n|match_BAN_TAU=1\u20131\n|match_BAN_V\u0116T=0\u20135\n\n|name_EKR=[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]\n|match_EKR_BAN=1\u20130\n|match_EKR_KRU=4\u20130\n|match_EKR_L&T=3\u20130\n|match_EKR_S\u016aD=2\u20132\n|match_EKR_\u0160IA=2\u20130\n|match_EKR_