fied for the [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|second]], while Tauras qualified for the [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|first qualifying round]] of the UEFA Europa League.\n|note_\u0160IA=V\u0116T\n|note_TAU=V\u0116T\n\n|col_CL2=#D0F0C0|text_CL2=Qualification to [[2010\u201311 UEFA Champions League#Second qualifying round|Champions League second qualifying round]]\n|result1=CL2\n|col_EL2=#BBEBFF|text_EL2=Qualification to [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|Europa League second qualifying round]]\n|result3=EL2|result4=EL2\n|col_EL1=#CCF3FF|text_EL1=Qualification to [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|Europa League first qualifying round]]\n|result5=EL1\n\n|update=complete\n|source=[https://web.archive.org/web/20090410022453/http://www.futbolas.lt/lt/lygos/a-lyga futbolas.lt] {{in lang|lt}}\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) head-to-head points; 3) head-to-head goal difference; 4) head-to-head goals scored; 5) goal difference; 6) number of goals scored.\n}}\n\n==Results==\nEvery team will play each other four times, twice at home and twice on the road, for a total of 28 games.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{#invoke:sports results|main\n|title=First half of season\n|matches_style=FBR|solid_cell=grey\n|team1=BAN|team2=EKR|team3=KRU|team4=L&T|team5=S\u016aD\n|team6=\u0160IA|team7=TAU|team8=V\u0116T\n\n|name_BAN=[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]\n|match_BAN_EKR=1\u20132\n|match_BAN_KRU=3\u20130\n|match_BAN_L&T=1\u20130\n|match_BAN_S\u016aD=0\u20130\n|match_BAN_\u0160IA=3\u20132\n|match_BAN_TAU=1\u20131\n|match_BAN_V\u0116T=0\u20135\n\n|name_EKR=[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]\n|match_EKR_BAN=1\u20130\n|match_EKR_KRU=4\u20130\n|match_EKR_L&T=3\u20130\n|match_EKR_S\u016aD=2\u20132\n|match_EKR_\u0160IA=2\u20130\n|match_EKR_TAU=2\u20131\n|match_EKR_V\u0116T=2\u20133\n\n|name_KRU=[[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]\n|match_KRU_BAN=2\u20130\n|match_KRU_EKR=2\u20132\n|match_KRU_L&T=1\u20131\n|match_KRU_S\u016a