{"title_page": "David Seville", "text_new": "{{About|a fictional character|the creator of ''Alvin and the Chipmunks''| Ross Bagdasarian Sr.}}\n{{short description|Fictional human}}\n{{Infobox character\n| series            = [[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n| name              = David Seville\n| gender            = Male\n| portrayer         = [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]]\n| voice = Ross Bagdasarian Sr. (1958\u201372) <br>[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] (1979\u2013)\n| creator           = [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]]\n| image             = <!-- Image needs to be added. -->\n| lbl21             = Other names\n| data21            = Dave Seville\n| first             = 1958\n| lbl1              = Years\n| data1             = ''[[The Alvin Show]]'' (1961\u20131962)<br>''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' (1983\u201390)<br>[[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film]] (1987\u20132015)<br>''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|ALVINNN!!! and the Chipmunks]]'' (2015\u2013present)\n| lbl2              = Home\n| data2             = The Seville Household with [[Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n| lbl3              = Classification\n| data3             = {{flat list|\n*[[List of Alvin and the Chipmunks episodes|Present Role]]\n*[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|2015 Series]]\n*[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip|The Road Chip]]\n}}\n| occupation        = Producer<br>Manager<br>Father of [[Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n| children          = {{flat list|\n*[[Alvin Seville|Alvin]]\n*[[Simon Seville|Simon]]\n*[[Theodore Seville|Theodore]]\n*[[Brittany Miller|Brittany]]\n*[[The Chipettes|Jeanette]]\n*[[Eleanor Miller|Eleanor]]\n}}\n| family            = Toby Seville\n| relatives     = Jackie Seville (Aunt)\n| significant_other = \n| nationality       = [[United States|American]]\n| lbl31             = Official website\n| data31            = http://www.chipmunks.com\n}}\n\n'''David \"Dave\" Seville''' is a fictional character, the producer and manager of the fictional singing group ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks]]''. The character was created by [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]] Bagdasarian had used the name \"David Seville\" as his [[stage name]] prior to the creation of the Chipmunks, while writing and recording [[Novelty song|novelty records]] in the 1950s.<ref name= \"angry\">{{cite news |last=Blevins |first=Joe |url= http://www.vulture.com/2015/11/the-dark-angry-father-of-alvin-and-the-chipmunks.html |title=The Dark, Angry Father of \u2018Alvin and the Chipmunks\u2019 |work=[[Splitsider]] |date=November 10, 2015 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> One of the records, recorded under the David Seville stage name, was \"[[Witch Doctor (song)|Witch Doctor]]\", featuring a sped-up high-pitched vocal technique that Bagdasarian would later use in \"[[The Chipmunk Song (Christmas Don't Be Late)]]\", which would introduce both Alvin and the Chipmunks as a singing group and Bagdasarian's [[music producer]] \"Dave\". Bagdasarian would go on to create ''[[The Alvin Show]]'', based on the Alvin and the Chipmunks group, where he voiced the semi-fictional character David Seville,<ref name= \"Blu-Ray\">{{cite news |last=Beck |first=Jerry |url= https://www.indiewire.com/2015/01/the-alvin-show-coming-to-blu-ray-123683/ |title=\"The Alvin Show\" Coming to Blu-Ray |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=January 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> based largely on himself, with Alvin based on Ross's sometimes rebellious son Adam.<ref name=\"angry\"/>\n\nLittle known \"Chipmunk fact,\" David Seville is actually secretly David Bowie the whole time. Boy does David Bowie love the little freaks. \n\nBagdasarian Sr. died in 1972, and his son (Adam's brother) [[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] took over ownership of [[Bagdasarian Productions]]. He reprised the David Seville character, first in a series of novelty albums beginning with 1980's ''[[Chipmunk Punk]]''.<ref name= \"CPunk\">{{cite news |last=Rayl |first=Salley; Bell, Bonnie |url= https://people.com/archive/chipmunk-punk-yep-those-amazing-animals-alvin-simon-theodore-have-chirped-back-onto-the-charts-vol-14-no-16/ |title=Chipmunk Punk? Yep, Those Amazing Animals\u2014Alvin, Simon & Theodore\u2014have Chirped Back Onto the Charts |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=October 20, 1980 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> Bagdasarian Jr. subsequently assumed the role on the TV series ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'', which ran in original episodes from 1983\u20131990. Bagdasarian Jr. has voiced David Seville in all official animated and recorded incarnations of David Seville since taking over for his father in the 1970s, including TV series, animated specials, and [[direct-to-video]] productions. He most recently voiced the character in the [[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|2015 reboot]] of the ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' television show.\n\nActor [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] also portrays David Seville in a [[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film|live action/CGI films starring Alvin and the Chipmunks]] which uses a combination of live-action acting and [[computer animation]].<ref name= \"Lee\">{{cite news |last=Radish |first=Christina |url= http://collider.com/jason-lee-alvin-and-the-chipmunks-chipwrecked-interview/ |title=Jason Lee ALVIN AND THE CHIPMUNKS: CHIPWRECKED Interview |work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=December 13, 2011 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> While Ross Bagdasarian, Jr. does not do any voices for the film series, the films are all produced in association with Bagdasarian Productions, which owns the rights to all of the characters.\n\n==Portrayed by==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Portrayed by !! TV Series  !! Film Series  !! Air Date !! Year !! Notes \n|-\n| [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]] || ''[[The Alvin Show]]''  ||{{N/A|}}|| 1961\u201362  || 1950s\u201372 || Creator\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" {{yes}} ||1983\u20131990 || rowspan=\"2\"|1979\u2013present  || rowspan=\"2\"| Producer & Voice\n|-\n| [[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|ALVINNN and the Chipmunks]] || 2015\u2013present\n|-\n| [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] ||{{N/A|}}|| [[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film|Film Series]] || 2007\u2013present ||{{N/A|}} || [[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film|live action/CGI films]]\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n{{Main|Alvin and the Chipmunks in film}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Portrayed By !! Production !! Producer\n|-\n| 1987 || ''[[The Chipmunk Adventure]]'' ||rowspan=\"8\"|Main Role || rowspan=\"4\"|[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.|Ross Bagdasarian]] || [[Bagdasarian Productions]] || Ross Bagdasarian, Jr.\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks Meet Frankenstein]]'' || rowspan=\"2\"|Bagdasarian Company<br/>[[Universal Animation Studios|Universal Cartoon Studios]] || rowspan=\"2\"|Kathi Castillo\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks Meet the Wolfman]]''\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Little Alvin and the Mini-Munks]]''  || Bagdasarian Company<br/>[[Paramount Pictures]] || Ross Bagdasarian, Jr.\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (film)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' || rowspan=\"4\"|[[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] || rowspan=\"5\"|[[20th Century Fox|Fox 2000 Pictures]]<br>[[Regency Enterprises]]<br>Bagdasarian Company || rowspan=\"4\"| Janice Karman<br>Ross Bagdasarian, Jr.\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]''\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip]]''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{{further|Bagdasarian Productions}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Voice by !! Notes\n|-\n| 1961\u201362 || ''[[The Alvin Show]]'' || rowspan=\"4\"|Main || [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]] || October 1961\n|-\n| 1983\u201390 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' || rowspan=\"3\"|[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] || Original Series\n|-\n| 2015\u2013present || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|ALVINNN!!! and the Chipmunks]]'' || Started August 2015\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* {{section link|Alvin and the Chipmunks|Main characters}}\n* {{section link|Ross Bagdasarian, Sr.|Discography (without the Chipmunks)}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Alvin and the Chipmunks}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Seville, David}}\n[[Category:Alter egos]]\n[[Category:Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n\n\n{{animation-char-stub}}\n{{Fict-char-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{About|a fictional character|the creator of ''Alvin and the Chipmunks''| Ross Bagdasarian Sr.}}\n{{short description|Fictional human}}\n{{Infobox character\n| series            = [[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n| name              = David Seville\n| gender            = Male\n| portrayer         = [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]]\n| voice = Ross Bagdasarian Sr. (1958\u201372) <br>[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] (1979\u2013)\n| creator           = [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]]\n| image             = <!-- Image needs to be added. -->\n| lbl21             = Other names\n| data21            = Dave Seville\n| first             = 1958\n| lbl1              = Years\n| data1             = ''[[The Alvin Show]]'' (1961\u20131962)<br>''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' (1983\u201390)<br>[[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film]] (1987\u20132015)<br>''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|ALVINNN!!! and the Chipmunks]]'' (2015\u2013present)\n| lbl2              = Home\n| data2             = The Seville Household with [[Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n| lbl3              = Classification\n| data3             = {{flat list|\n*[[List of Alvin and the Chipmunks episodes|Present Role]]\n*[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|2015 Series]]\n*[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip|The Road Chip]]\n}}\n| occupation        = Producer<br>Manager<br>Father of [[Alvin and the Chipmunks]]\n| children          = {{flat list|\n*[[Alvin Seville|Alvin]]\n*[[Simon Seville|Simon]]\n*[[Theodore Seville|Theodore]]\n*[[Brittany Miller|Brittany]]\n*[[The Chipettes|Jeanette]]\n*[[Eleanor Miller|Eleanor]]\n}}\n| family            = Toby Seville\n| relatives     = Jackie Seville (Aunt)\n| significant_other = \n| nationality       = [[United States|American]]\n| lbl31             = Official website\n| data31            = http://www.chipmunks.com\n}}\n\n'''David \"Dave\" Seville''' is a fictional character, the producer and manager of the fictional singing group ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks]]''. The character was created by [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]] Bagdasarian had used the name \"David Seville\" as his [[stage name]] prior to the creation of the Chipmunks, while writing and recording [[Novelty song|novelty records]] in the 1950s.<ref name= \"angry\">{{cite news |last=Blevins |first=Joe |url= http://www.vulture.com/2015/11/the-dark-angry-father-of-alvin-and-the-chipmunks.html |title=The Dark, Angry Father of \u2018Alvin and the Chipmunks\u2019 |work=[[Splitsider]] |date=November 10, 2015 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> One of the records, recorded under the David Seville stage name, was \"[[Witch Doctor (song)|Witch Doctor]]\", featuring a sped-up high-pitched vocal technique that Bagdasarian would later use in \"[[The Chipmunk Song (Christmas Don't Be Late)]]\", which would introduce both Alvin and the Chipmunks as a singing group and Bagdasarian's [[music producer]] \"Dave\". Bagdasarian would go on to create ''[[The Alvin Show]]'', based on the Alvin and the Chipmunks group, where he voiced the semi-fictional character David Seville,<ref name= \"Blu-Ray\">{{cite news |last=Beck |first=Jerry |url= https://www.indiewire.com/2015/01/the-alvin-show-coming-to-blu-ray-123683/ |title=\"The Alvin Show\" Coming to Blu-Ray |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=January 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> based largely on himself, with Alvin based on Ross's sometimes rebellious son Adam.<ref name=\"angry\"/>\n\nBagdasarian Sr. died in 1972, and his son (Adam's brother) [[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] took over ownership of [[Bagdasarian Productions]]. He reprised the David Seville character, first in a series of novelty albums beginning with 1980's ''[[Chipmunk Punk]]''.<ref name= \"CPunk\">{{cite news |last=Rayl |first=Salley; Bell, Bonnie |url= https://people.com/archive/chipmunk-punk-yep-those-amazing-animals-alvin-simon-theodore-have-chirped-back-onto-the-charts-vol-14-no-16/ |title=Chipmunk Punk? Yep, Those Amazing Animals\u2014Alvin, Simon & Theodore\u2014have Chirped Back Onto the Charts |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=October 20, 1980 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> Bagdasarian Jr. subsequently assumed the role on the TV series ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'', which ran in original episodes from 1983\u20131990. Bagdasarian Jr. has voiced David Seville in all official animated and recorded incarnations of David Seville since taking over for his father in the 1970s, including TV series, animated specials, and [[direct-to-video]] productions. He most recently voiced the character in the [[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|2015 reboot]] of the ''Alvin and the Chipmunks'' television show.\n\nActor [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] also portrays David Seville in a [[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film|live action/CGI films starring Alvin and the Chipmunks]] which uses a combination of live-action acting and [[computer animation]].<ref name= \"Lee\">{{cite news |last=Radish |first=Christina |url= http://collider.com/jason-lee-alvin-and-the-chipmunks-chipwrecked-interview/ |title=Jason Lee ALVIN AND THE CHIPMUNKS: CHIPWRECKED Interview |work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=December 13, 2011 |accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref> While Ross Bagdasarian, Jr. does not do any voices for the film series, the films are all produced in association with Bagdasarian Productions, which owns the rights to all of the characters.\n\n==Portrayed by==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Portrayed by !! TV Series  !! Film Series  !! Air Date !! Year !! Notes \n|-\n| [[Ross Bagdasarian Sr.]] || ''[[The Alvin Show]]''  ||{{N/A|}}|| 1961\u201362  || 1950s\u201372 || Creator\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.]] || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" {{yes}} ||1983\u20131990 || rowspan=\"2\"|1979\u2013present  || rowspan=\"2\"| Producer & Voice\n|-\n| [[Alvin and the Chipmunks (2015 TV series)|ALVINNN and the Chipmunks]] || 2015\u2013present\n|-\n| [[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] ||{{N/A|}}|| [[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film|Film Series]] || 2007\u2013present ||{{N/A|}} || [[Alvin and the Chipmunks in film|live action/CGI films]]\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n{{Main|Alvin and the Chipmunks in film}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Portrayed By !! Production !! Producer\n|-\n| 1987 || ''[[The Chipmunk Adventure]]'' ||rowspan=\"8\"|Main Role || rowspan=\"4\"|[[Ross Bagdasarian Jr.|Ross Bagdasarian]] || [[Bagdasarian Productions]] || Ross Bagdasarian, Jr.\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks Meet Frankenstein]]'' || rowspan=\"2\"|Bagdasarian Company<br/>[[Universal Animation Studios|Universal Cartoon Studios]] || rowspan=\"2\"|Kathi Castillo\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks Meet the Wolfman]]''\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Little Alvin and the Mini-Munks]]''  || Bagdasarian Company<br/>[[Paramount Pictures]] || Ross Bagdasarian, Jr.\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (film)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]'' || rowspan=\"4\"|[[Jason Lee (actor)|Jason Lee]] || rowspan=\"5\"|[[20th Century Fox|Fox 2000 Pictures]]<br>[[Regency Enterprises]]<br>Bagdasarian Company || rowspan=\"4\"| Janice Karman<br>Ross Bagdasarian, Jr.\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]''\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked]]''\n|-\n